# React pages

## Hooks before returns

All `useState`, `useEffect`, `useMemo`, `useCallback`, and custom hooks must run **before** any early `return` (auth, loading, redirects). Never call hooks after `if (loading) return …`.

## Keep pages thin

- **Page file:** route params, layout shell, compose hooks + child components.
- **Extract** when a section grows: `src/components/<feature>/`, `src/hooks/use<Feature>.ts`, `src/lib/<feature>/`.
- **Artifact detail** (`artifact-detail/**`, `ArtifactDetailPage`): add UI in `components/framework/artifact-detail/`, logic in hooks under `src/hooks/`, not inline in the page.

## No god files

If a page approaches **1600 lines**, plan a split (hooks + section components). **2000 lines is a hard stop**—do not add features to an oversized page without extracting first.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hook after early return
if (loading) return null;
const x = useMemo(() => …, []);

// ✅ GOOD — hooks first, then guards
const x = useMemo(() => …, []);
if (loading) return null;
```
